.ti 0
Abstract

Because of the inevitable debate of trivial items at the Hacklab hacker space, it is clear that a standard, agreed-upon protocol for bickering over policy is established. Ironically, the agreement of such a standard may, itself, be subject to being "bikeshedded". The preemptive drafting of this document aims to mitigate such a recursive problem.

.ti 0
Status of this Memo

This document specifies a horrible, non-efficient, policy-setting protocol for the Hacklab community, and requests discussion and suggestions for improvements ("bikeshedding"). Distribution of this memo is unlimited.

